### ✅ ** BVA – University Grading System (A: 90–100, B: 80–89, C: 70–79, D: 60–69)**

| Test Case Type | Scenario    | Test Case ID      | Title                     | Step ID | Step Action        | Expected Result                   |
| -------------- | ----------- | ----------------- | ------------------------- | ------- | ------------------ | --------------------------------- |
| Boundary       | Score = 59  | TC\_BVA\_GRD\_001 | Below Grade D             | STP\_01 | Enter score as 59  | Grade F or Fail assigned          |
| Boundary       | Score = 60  | TC\_BVA\_GRD\_002 | Lower boundary of Grade D | STP\_01 | Enter score as 60  | Grade D assigned                  |
| Boundary       | Score = 61  | TC\_BVA\_GRD\_003 | Just above lower Grade D  | STP\_01 | Enter score as 61  | Grade D assigned                  |
| Boundary       | Score = 99  | TC\_BVA\_GRD\_004 | Just below max            | STP\_01 | Enter score as 99  | Grade A assigned                  |
| Boundary       | Score = 100 | TC\_BVA\_GRD\_005 | Upper boundary of Grade A | STP\_01 | Enter score as 100 | Grade A assigned                  |
| Boundary       | Score = 101 | TC\_BVA\_GRD\_006 | Above Grade A             | STP\_01 | Enter score as 101 | Error: "Score out of valid range" |

